Leicester Tigers beat London Welsh 38-17 in the Aviva Premiership on Saturday . 
  Chris Hala'ufia halted Laurence Pearce with a shoulder charge and shoved his head into the ground . 
  The Tongan was then sent off for a brutal attack on the Leicester forward . 
  Leicester fought back from a 10-7 half time deficit to win . 
  Koree Britton and Opeti Fonua scored tries for London Welsh . 
  Ben Youngs scored two tries for Leicester . 
 